<subSubSection id="95D82CCE26BFB2A7536B727665DD7D42" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="C7C031B02296AB006530DA43F1786CF8" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E68C6B829DD185E7B1C11419618C30F3" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Body colour translucent white, yellow to orange-yellow ridges, and several dark spots anteriorly and posteriorly near mantle edge. Foot translucent white with at least one black spot near tip and broad pale yellow margin. Rhinophores long, translucent white with one dark brown spot on stalk; yellow on proximal third, dark brown on distal two-thirds of lamellate portion, white on elongated tip. Six gills white with black band across inner side of each rachis from base to tips of pinnules.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B0D3322305D34C4C3DB3FEEEA55310AC" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2079673B2096E82B2B0D2DE453DB27EB" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B0517C2AC5508985F0447023D1A84247" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
This small species was first recognised by 
<bibRefCitation id="95BD0F0654587FA98DB43E456811E181" author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Revue francaise d'aquariologie herpetologie" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 30" title="Opisthobranches de l'lle Maurice, avec la description de deux especes nouvelles (Mollusca: Opisthobranchia)." volume="18" year="1991">Yonow and Hayward (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, based upon specimens collected from Mauritius and La 
<normalizedToken id="EA0CF5C912109053EA33ECAB4F1B9A0E" originalValue="Réunion">Reunion</normalizedToken>
, the type locality. Three specimens from Western Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="D3360BB8233343E1467F9A54234ACBB0" author="Fahey, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino Malacologico Roma" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="55 - 76" title="On the genus Halgerda (Nudibranchia: Halgerdidae) from Western Australia with descriptions of four new species." volume="37" year="2001">Fahey and Gosliner 2001</bibRefCitation>
) extend the range of this species to the eastern Indian Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
